  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/clarium/b8a3f34e-5c23-4544-b599-5d6b9ad015a1/application",
    "company": "Clarium",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "923991ef9d600d59",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Why Clarium?\n\nOur mission is to accelerate healthcare transformation through our AI-powered platform. We strive toward a future where hospitals are at the cutting edge of technology, operations and efficiency. Healthcare workers are inundated with endless tasks, manual processes and often unintuitive tools. Clarium is transforming healthcare by empowering providers with AI-powered software with intelligent workflow automation and actionable insights.\n\nWe envision a future where all hospitals leverage our collaborative data platform to automate their daily operational and administrative tasks, only surfacing high complexity issues that truly require their expertise.\n\nWe're backed by some of the biggest and most innovative investors in the world including: Northzone, General Catalyst, AlleyCorp, 1984 Ventures, Alumni Ventures, and others.\n\nRole Overview\n\nWe’re hiring a Forward Deployed Engineer (Data) to own the technical side of customer data integrations for hospital systems and their suppliers. This role is for a strong, hands-on engineer who enjoys working directly with customers, navigating ambiguous systems, and owning production data workflows end to end.\n\nYou’ll work directly with customers to understand their systems and bring integrations into production, designing reliable ingestion and transformation workflows along the way. You’ll partner closely with data engineers and product managers to iterate on customer data feeds that power end-user features, ensure integrations are correct and production-ready, and build reusable connectors and internal tools that make future integrations faster and more scalable.\n\nThis role goes beyond traditional backend engineering. Success requires comfort with ambiguity, unfamiliar systems, and frequent customer interaction, along with full ownership of production systems. If you enjoy building robust systems and staying close to the customer problems they solve, this role is a strong fit.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n - 4+ years of professional experience in an engineering role\n\n - Strong proficiency in Python and SQL\n\n - Experience building and operating data pipelines\n\n - Experience with strong engineering practices including building production grade systems, robust ETL pipelines, CI/CD, and monitoring\n\n - Experience with AWS or similar cloud platforms\n\n - Ability to work directly with clients to gather requirements, troubleshoot, and deliver integrations\n\nNice-to-Haves\n\n - Experience integrating with\n   \n   - ERP systems such as Workday, Oracle Cloud, Infor Lawson, PeopleSoft, or similar\n   \n   - Inventory Management systems such as ParEx and TecSys\n   \n   - EHR systems such as Epic or Cerner\n\n - Experience in healthcare\n\n - Experience in supply chain operations\n\nWhat Makes You a Great Fit\n\n - Agency — You’re a self-starter who’s comfortable with ambiguous requirements and unfamiliar systems, and you know how to unblock yourself when things get messy.\n\n - Ownership — You take responsibility for outcomes, not just tasks, and you jump in where needed to support customer integrations and the broader team, even when it’s not “your job.”\n\n - Customer-facing mindset — You enjoy working directly with customers, leading technical discussions, and translating real-world workflows into reliable data integrations.\n\n - Collaborative — You thrive in a close-knit data team, value low-ego collaboration, and work effectively with data engineers, product managers, and customers.\n\n - Pragmatic — You make thoughtful technical tradeoffs, balancing immediate customer needs with long-term scalability and maintainability.\n\n - Operational excellence — You value production quality, including testing, CI/CD, monitoring, and building systems that are reliable and maintainable in the real world.\n\nNote: This role is not a fit for engineers seeking purely backend or internal-only work, analysts or BI-focused roles without experience building production systems, or those who prefer working independently over close, team-first collaboration.\n\nWhat You Get At Clarium\n\n - Incentive Stock Options proportionate to salary\n\n - Fully remote work\n\n - Unlimited PTO\n\n - Top-tier health, vision, and dental benefits\n\nOur Hiring Process\n\nApply\n\nWe read every application and make our best effort to reply to everyone. Please read the job description carefully. We love when people strive but if you do not meet more than 75% of the requirements, we are less likely to respond. Please take your time on any application questions—we view them as your opportunity to stand out.\n\nExploratory Interview\n\nGoal: High-level qualifications \u0026 mutual fit. 30-minute video interview with a team member who knows the product and role well. We make sure to preserve 10 minutes for your questions.\n\nHiring Manager Interview\n\nGoal: Deeper understanding of team needs and your qualifications. 30-minute video interview with the hiring manager.\n\nTechnical Interview and System Design Interview\n\nGoal: Deep dive into your skills, knowledge, and problem solving. 1-hour technical exercise using Python and SQL as well as a 1-hour System Design Exercise. This is a realistic interview with no abstract puzzles. We will send you information in advance and do a live exercise together. Screen sharing is expected.\n\nValues and CEO Interview:\n\nGoal: Meet more of the team and understand what values are important to you. 30-minute video interview with the manager of the role to feel comfortable with each other one final time and 30 minutes to get to know our CEO.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
